<!-- ── FORMULA ── -->
<section class="content-section reveal">
  <h2>The Formula</h2>
  <p>The payment is calculated using the standard annuity formula:</p>
  <div class="formula-box">
    M = P &times; [r(1 + r)<sup>n</sup>] &divide; [(1 + r)<sup>n</sup> &minus; 1]
  </div>
  <p>Where:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>M</strong> = payment amount (monthly or biweekly)</li>
    <li><strong>P</strong> = loan principal (amount borrowed)</li>
    <li><strong>r</strong> = periodic interest rate (annual rate &divide; number of periods per year)</li>
    <li><strong>n</strong> = total number of payments (years &times; periods per year)</li>
  </ul>
  <p>For monthly payments, <strong>r</strong> = annual rate &divide; 12 and <strong>n</strong> = years &times; 12. For biweekly, <strong>r</strong> = annual rate &divide; 26 and <strong>n</strong> = years &times; 26.</p>
  <p><strong>Total interest</strong> = (M &times; n) &minus; P. This is the true cost of borrowing — the amount you pay above the original loan.</p>
</section>

